Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["# Classical Growth Model with Endogenous Saving Rates",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\nThis Wolfram Mathematica notebook explores the dynamics of a **Classical \
Growth Model** where saving rates are determined endogenously. Unlike the \
standard Solow model, this version incorporates a subsistence consumption \
constraint, leading to non-linear dynamics and the potential for multiple \
equilibria (poverty traps vs. steady-state growth).\n\n## Theoretical \
Framework\nThe endogenous saving rate is based on the work of King and Rebelo",
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ", modeled through a Stone-Geary utility/consumption function. This setup \
assumes that agents must satisfy a minimum level of consumption before they \
can begin to save effectively.\n\n### Key Parameters:\n\[Alpha]:  \
Productivity of capital (output elasticity).\nz:  Subsistence consumption \
level.\n\[Psi]: Subsistence product (minimum required output).\n\[Phi]: \
Propensity to consume above the subsistence threshold.\nn: Population growth \
rate.\n\[Delta]: Depreciation rate of capital.\n---\n\n",
 StyleBox["## Notebook Contents",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\nThe notebook is organized into three interactive `Manipulate` sections to \
visualize the model\[CloseCurlyQuote]s mechanics:\n\n1. **Diagram**: A visual \
decomposition of the capital accumulation equation, showing the intersection \
of the saving function and the break-even investment line ($n + \\delta$).\n\
2. **Phase Portrait**: A dynamic view of the change in capital over time \
($\\dot{k}$), highlighting how the system evolves from different initial \
conditions.\n3. **Vectors**: A 1D vector field representation showing the \
direction of flow along the capital axis, identifying the stable ($k^*$) and \
unstable ($k_{\\psi}$) equilibria.\n---\n\n",
 StyleBox["## \:26a0\:fe0f Prerequisites & Setup",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\nThis notebook uses the ",
 StyleBox["MaTeX ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "package by Szabolcs Horv\[AAcute]t to render high-quality $\\LaTeX$ labels \
within the plots.\n\n1. **Install MaTeX**: You must have the package \
installed. You can find it at [github.com/szhorvat/MaTeX].\n2. **Enable \
MaTeX**: Before running the `Manipulate` cells, you must initialize the \
package. An **\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]Enable MaTeX\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]** \
initialization cell is provided at the beginning of each section for \
convenience.\n3. **Ghostscript**: MaTeX requires a working installation of \
Ghostscript on your system to function correctly.\n"
}], "Text",
